gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 130, Lakers 120
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by De'Aaron Fox's career-high tying 44 points, the Kings defeated the Lakers, 130-120. Fox added four rebounds, four assists and two steals for the Kings, while Domantas Sabonis put up his league-leading 22nd triple-double of the season as he recorded 16 points, 20 rebounds and 12 assists in the victory. LeBron James tallied 31 points, five rebounds and 13 assists for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 35-26 on the season, while the Lakers fall to 34-30.
